                    brings real world challenges, especially from partners in Cuba, Ethiopia, Kenya, Tanzania, and Uganda, directly into the curriculum 
                    through Problem Based Learning (PBL) and Work Integrated Learning (WIL), ensuring solutions are beneficial for local communities.
                    DI4D strengthens digital skills and innovation capacity, promotes inclusive participation with a particular focus on women and 
                    learners with fewer opportunities. It fosters long term collaborations across academia, civil society, government, and the private sector.
                </p>
